D%D0%B8%D0%BA%D0%B8_%D0%B2%D0%BE%D0%B9%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%BE%D0%B9_=
%D1%80%D0%B0%D0%B7%D0%B2%D0%B5%D0%B4%D0%BA%D0%B8%C2%BB_%D0%90%D0%A0%D0%9C%D=
0%98-2017_%288%29.jpg" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"250" height=3D"167" clas=
s=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D"1200" data-file-height=3D"800"></a=
><figcaption>Soldier on the left displaying the clamp-style bipod</figcapti=
on></figure>
<p>The SVD was used by <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Designated_=
marksman" title=3D"Designated marksman">designated marksmen</a> designated =
in the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soviet_Army" title=3D"Sovie=
t Army">Soviet Army</a> as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Snipers=
_of_the_Soviet_Union" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Snipers of the Soviet =
Union">snipers</a> at the basic <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Me=
chanized_infantry" title=3D"Mechanized infantry">motorized infantry</a> <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Platoon#USSR_organization" title=3D"P=
latoon">rifle platoon</a> level.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-31" class=3D"reference"=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SVD_(rifle)#cite_note-31"><span c=
lass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>31<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></=
sup> For this purpose, the rifle was designed to be much lighter than more =
conventional precision rifles, making it better suited for use by infantry,=
 and the rifle is <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Self-loading_rif=
le" title=3D"Self-loading rifle">autoloading</a> in order to prioritize vol=
ume of fire over precision. It was thought that a relatively small number o=
f marksmen armed with 7.62=C3=9754mmR <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Fully_powered_cartridge" title=3D"Fully powered cartridge">fully powere=
d cartridge</a> chambered arms could assist conventional troops armed with =
7.62=C3=9739mm <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intermediate_cartri=
dge" title=3D"Intermediate cartridge">intermediate cartridge</a> chambered =
arms by suppressing/harassing valuable targets and assets (such as <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Officer_(armed_forces)" title=3D"Officer =
(armed forces)">officers</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radi=
oman" title=3D"Radioman">radio operators</a>, vehicle crews, other marksmen=
, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Machine_gun" title=3D"Machine gu=
n">machine gun</a> teams, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anti-tan=
k_warfare" title=3D"Anti-tank warfare">anti-tank warfare</a> teams, etc.) w=
ith greater precision and at much greater ranges.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-32" cl=
ass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SVD_(rifle)#cite=
_note-32"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>32<span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Once the rifle had been produced in sufficient numbers, every <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Warsaw_Pact" title=3D"Warsaw Pact">Warsa=
w Pact</a> infantry <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Platoon" title=
=3D"Platoon">platoon</a> included at least one SVD-equipped marksman. In th=
e <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/German_Democratic_Republic" clas=
s=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"German Democratic Republic">German Democratic Re=
public</a> arsenals, there were almost 1,750.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-33" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SVD_(rifle)#cite_no=
te-33"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>33<span class=3D"cite-bracket">=
]</span></a></sup> The marksmen were often chosen from personnel who displa=
yed exceptional rifle marksmanship while members of <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/DOSAAF" title=3D"DOSAAF">DOSAAF</a>. Such marksmen were e=
stimated to have a 50% probability of hitting a standing, man-sized target =
at 800&nbsp;m (875&nbsp;yd), and an 80% probability of hitting a standing, =
man-sized target at 500&nbsp;m (547&nbsp;yd). To attain this level of accur=
acy, the sniper could not engage more than two such targets per minute. For=
 distances not exceeding 200&nbsp;m (219&nbsp;yd), the probability was esti=
mated to be well above 90% regardless of the time taken.<sup id=3D"cite_ref=
-34" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SVD_(rifl=
e)#cite_note-34"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>34<span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
